You can create unlimited projects with any emoji prefix!

## Task Status Management

Tasks are managed through status emojis in your daily markdown files. To change a task's status, simply edit the emoji at the end of the task line.

The default status workflow is:
- ğŸ“ Planned (excluded from reports)
- âš¡ In Progress
- ğŸš§ Blocked
- ğŸ“… Rescheduled
- â¡ï¸ Carried Forward
- âœ… Completed (not carried forward)
- ğŸš« Cancelled

Example of changing task status:
```markdown
# Original task
- [ ] Review documentation ğŸ“

# Change to in-progress
- [ ] Review documentation âš¡

# Mark as completed
- [ ] Review documentation âœ…
```

Status behaviors:
- Tasks marked as âœ… (completed) won't carry forward to the next day
- Tasks marked as ğŸš« (cancelled) won't carry forward
- Tasks with ğŸ“ (planned) status are excluded from EOD reports
- All other tasks will carry forward with â¡ï¸ status

## Output Formats

TaskDaily supports multiple output formats:

### Slack
```bash
daily share --format slack
```
- Proper emoji codes (e.g., :memo:)
- Clean bullet points (â—‹ for todo, â— for done)
- Section dividers

### Microsoft Teams
```bash
daily share --format teams
```
- Markdown formatting
- Proper headers
- Task checkboxes (â˜, â˜‘)

### WhatsApp
```bash
daily share --format whatsapp
```
- Bold headers
- Simple formatting
- Unicode bullets

### Email
```bash
daily share --format email
```
- HTML formatting
- Clean lists
- Professional layout

## Configuration

The package uses a configuration file located at `~/.config/daily-task/config.yaml`. You can:

- Reset to defaults: `daily config init`
- View config paths: `daily config path`

### Customizing Status Workflow

Add or modify statuses in your config file:
```yaml
status:
  planned:
    name: "Planned"
    emoji: "ğŸ“"
    show_in_report: false
    carry_forward: true
  in_progress:
    name: "In Progress"
    emoji: "âš¡"
    show_in_report: true
    carry_forward: true
  completed:
    name: "Completed"
    emoji: "âœ…"
    show_in_report: true
    carry_forward: false
  # Add more statuses...
```

## Smart Features

1. Task Handling:
   - Completed tasks (âœ…) are not carried forward
   - Planned tasks (ğŸ“) are excluded from EOD reports
   - Tasks maintain their status when carried forward

2. Project Management:
   - Create unlimited projects
   - Use any emoji as project prefix
   - No configuration needed for new projects

3. Format Handling:
   - Each format has optimized styling
   - Preserves emojis and formatting
   - Maintains readability across platforms

